# Coding Standards — Never Do

- Use `any` (use `unknown` and narrow)
- Disable ESLint without justification
- Use `var` (use `const` or `let`)
- Mutate React state directly
- Use array index as React `key` for dynamic lists
- Store sensitive data in `localStorage`
- Use synchronous file I/O in API route handlers
